Actually no I would not. Being a Bard in GOD is VERY boring. We don't pull much as it is. Some pulling in Qvic because mobs are fast and its outdoors. But even there its a joke.<br>
<br>
We offer very little to raids anymore due to power gains of buffs and the way fights are very fast now. Mana is rarely an issue to casters anymore. Our DPS adds nothing to a raid. Resists are not needed at this level mainly because with buffs people are at or near the cap. Or they are irresistible anyways.<br>
<br>
Bards have very little to work toward as far as character advancement. Our AA are not only pathetic, they are so bad they make us angry to even look at. Our gear upgrade path is so limited and poorly thought out by SOE that there is little desire to keep playing. Like I have said before, what a POP/GOD equipped bard can bring to a raid is almost exactly the same as a bazaar equipped bard can bring. Mostly just more HP. /zzzzz <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=15483" target="top">Lanolar </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rytaneq>Rytan EQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#330000>(6/7/04 1:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19472.topic&index=66>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Letter from SoE from Summit</span><hr size=1> The Fading Memories comment came from me, although the portrayal on this board is rather inaccurate.<br>
<br>
There are no plans to nerf Fading Memories as it applies to current content.  There is the possibility of adding NPCs in the future who are more difficult to fade from, or possibly immune, but you won't see any chance to how FM currently works.<br>
<br>
Thanks to everyone who took the time to attend the summit and provide feedback.  It definitely helped us create and continue to solidify a list of priorities for EQ.<br>
